<TITLE> Minister fears militant attacks against WC trials </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 7 (bdnews24.com)  State minister for home Shamsul Haq Tuku has said that he fears they may be militant attacks ahead of the war crimes trial. "The anti-liberation forces might attempt to foil the trial in order to save the war criminals. All of us should remain alert to the evil forces," he told reporters after a meeting on Wednesday. The law enforcement agencies are active in trying to thwart any sabotage attempt, he said. "Whoever tries to create obstacles to the trials will not be successful," Tuku said. He said that attempts have already been made to destabilise the situation by these "forces" committing violence in academic institutions He however did not point to any specific intelligence in the possession of the government that such incidents are being planned. b
